      "content": "Those tiny, consistent losses are often caused by \"shrinkage\" from normal warehouse operations, such as packaging errors, minor misplacements during re-goods, or even the wear and tear of RFID tags causing false reads. Since the ERP logs don't show obvious theft, your team might be inadvertently writing off these items during routine cycle counting or applying a blanket adjustment for damaged packaging that isn't being reflected in the physical count. It could also be a systematic issue with the barcoding process, where items are scanned twice (once for receipt, once for shipping) but the second scan fails to update the system properly. I suggest focusing on process improvements like stricter cycle count protocols and reviewing your packaging procedures to see if the small discrepancies are being lost in transit or inventory handling.",
